text: The Sarangani–Sultan Kudarat Coastal Road or Awang–Upi–Lebak–Kalamansig–Palimbang–Sarangani Road is a 323-kilometre (201 mi), two-to-four lane national secondary road, connecting the provinces of Maguindanao, Sultan Kudarat, Sarangani, and South Cotabato. It starts from Datu Odin Sinsuat in Maguindanao and ends at General Santos in South Cotabato. The entire road is designated as the National Route 935 (N935) of the Philippine highway network. == Intersections == == References == Category:Roads in Mindanao
title: Sarangani–Sultan Kudarat Coastal Road
